Types : A type identifies a set of values ( and their representation in memory) and a set of operations that transform these values into other values of that set.
Java is strongly typed language.

Primitive Types , User-defined Types:

Primitive Types:

boolean - implementation dependent
char - 16 bits(stores unicode)
byte - 8 bits
short - 16 bits
int - 32 bits
long - 64 bits
float  - 32 bits 
double - 64 bits

variables Examples : int counter;
                     double temp;
                     String name;
                     int[] ages;
                     char letters[];
                     
constants:
integer constant consists of a sequence of digits.

if the constant is to represent a long integer value,it must be sufixed with an uppercase L or lowercase l.
if there is no suffix the constant represents 32 bit integer(an int).

Integer constant can be specified in the decimal, headecimal, octal or binary format
127
0x7f
0177
0b01101100
 

